KCNA Blasts Some Congressmen for Standing in Way of Six-Party Talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Some lawmakers from the Republican Party of the United States recently introduced a bill to Congress urging the U.S. not to de-list the DPRK as a sponsor of terrorism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ileana Ros-Lehtinen, member of the House of Representatives, who sponsored the bill, put up in the bill such unreasonable conditionalities as putting an end to cooperation in the field of development of banned military equipment and cooperation in the nuclear field with Syria, insisting that the U.S. policy toward the DPRK should not be based on the hope that it would honor its commitments but based on its actual performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is nothing but reckless remarks beclouding the prospect of the talks as they are intended to stem the trend of the times toward detente over the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula and put a brake on the process to advance the six-party talks and warm up the DPRK-U.S. relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK cannot overlook the brazen-faced remarks made by the U.S. chief executive against his dialogue partner on the international arena, timed to coincide with the introduction of the above-said bill by U.S. conservative hard-liners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, addressing the UN General Assembly on Sept. 25, went so reckless as to mention some countries including the DPRK and call them "brutal regimes". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The renewed accusation made by him against the DPRK was nothing but a foolish ploy to tarnish the DPRK's dignity and authority rising on the international arena as the days go by, which the servicepersons and people of the DPRK will never tolerate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  When judging this as the viewpoint of the U.S. chief executive, one can hardly guess the ever-changing U.S. view on the DPRK and talk about the bilateral confidence, the key to making progress at the six-party talks and the development of the bilateral relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Confidence building is vitally required by the countries participating in the six-party talks as the negotiated settlement of the nuclear issue is a very sensitive political issue related to peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula and the Asia-Pacific region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is by no means fortuitous that the international community is expressing concern and uneasiness about the moves being taken by the U.S. conservative hard-liners at a time when the six-party talks are progressing and the DPRK-U.S. relations are developing at a certain level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They invented various pretexts to lay hurdles in the way of the talks whenever there was some progress in them in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A lot of time has been wasted since the start of the talks. This was entirely attributable to the wrong view of the U.S. on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to pay attention to and ponder over the factors of adversely affecting the progress at the talks and the settlement of the nuclear issue and be consistent in its policy toward the DPRK, though belatedly.

Kim Yong Nam Meets S. Korean and Japanese Delegations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had talks with a delegation of the Yonhap News of south Korea led by Director General Kim Ki So and a delegation of the Kyodo News of Japan led by President Satoshi Ishikawa at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Hong Son Ok, vice-chairperson of the Korean Society for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Chang Gwang, deputy director general of the Korean Central News Agency, Pak Kyong Chol, vice-chairman of the National Reconciliation Council, and officials concerned.

Gift to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a gift from the president of the Kyodo News of Japan, on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, by President of the Kyodo News of Japan Satoshi Ishikawa on Friday.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Bulgarian Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a talk with Angel Orbetsov, Bulgarian ambassador to the DPRK who paid a farewell call on him, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Oct. 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Kim Hyong Jun, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and a staff member of the Bulgarian embassy.

Meeting Held to Commemorate Anniversaries of Revolutionary Schools 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held at the April 25 House of Culture on Friday to mark the 60th anniversaries of the foundation of the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and Kang Pan Sok Revolutionary School. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was attended by Kim Yong Nam, Kim Kyok Sik, Kim Il Chol, Kim Jong Gak, Choe Thae Bok, Kim Ki Nam, teachers and students of the schools and graduates from the schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants listened to the recorded speech made by President Kim Il Sung before the teachers and students of the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and graduates from it on the occasion of the 20th anniversary of its foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea to the teachers and students of the two schools was conveyed at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is immense pride and pleasure for the Party and the army and people of the DPRK to have such "pedigree" institutions for training hard core cadres who would carry forward the traditions of the Korean revolution as the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and Kang Pan Sok Revolutionary School, the message said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the belief that the teachers and students of the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and Kang Pan Sok Revolutionary School would bring about a fresh turn in the education of the bereaved children of revolutionaries true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il and thus live up to the deep trust and great expectation of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Gak in a report recalled that the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and Kang Pan Sok Revolutionary School have traversed a shining road of victory and glory under the wise guidance and warm care of the three generals of Mt. Paektu over the past 60 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung gave field guidance to the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School more than 110 times throughout his great life, setting it as a basic mission of the school to train reserve cadres of the People's Army and leading it with warm loving care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk, woman general of Mt. Paektu, even postponing the visit to her native place, saw to it that all the bereaved children of the comrades-in-arms who fell in action were brought to the school and a statue of the President was erected at the school for the first time in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il left immortal footprints at the two schools dozens of times since that historical day when he visited the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School to participate in its inaugural ceremony 60 years ago, energetically leading them to effect a fresh turn in education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and Kang Pan Sok Revolutionary School have been developed into reliable centers for carrying forward the revolutionary traditions replete with the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and the spirit of the red flag of Mt. Paektu and model schools for bereaved children of revolutionaries equipped with modern amenities for education and living, the reporter noted, adding that this is entirely thanks to the wise guidance and warm fatherly love shown by the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called for bringing about a fresh turn in education of the schools true to the Songun leadership of the Party and thus making a positive contribution to achieving the reunification of the country and accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting.

Congratulations to Ethiopian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Friday sent a congratulatory message to Girma Wolde-Giorgis upon his reelection as President of Ethiopia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the long-standing friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to grow strong, Kim Yong Nam in the message sincerely wished the president good health and greater success in his responsible work for peace, stability and prosperity of the country.

Greetings to Jamaican Prime Minister 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Il, premier of the Cabinet of the DPRK, sent a message of greetings to Bruce Golding upon his appointment as Prime Minister of Jamaica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the expectation and belief that the friendly relations between the two countries would continue to develop on good terms, the message wished the prime minister success in his responsible work for the development of the country and the well-being of the people.

Greetings to Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade of Jamaica 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- DPRK Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun sent a message of greetings to Kenneth Baugh upon his appointment as minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade of Jamaica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed the expectation and belief that cooperation between the foreign ministries for the continued expansion and development of the bilateral relations would grow stronger.

Polish Embassy Officials Help Korean Farmers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Ambassador Roman Iwaszkiewicz and members of the Polish embassy here helped farmers of the DPRK-Poland Friendship Jangsuwon Co-op Farm in Samsok District in rice-harvesting on October 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During a break, they enjoyed an art performance given by kindergartners of the farm and had conversation with the officials of the farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They conveyed aid materials to the farm.

"Breeding Farm" for Rearing Pivots of Revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Mangyongdae Revolutionary School greets its 60th birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The school located in the sacred land of revolution is the centre of life and study for the bereaved children of revolutionaries, which was established on the direct initiative of President Kim Il Sung and under his guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Under the warm care of the three Generals of Mt. Paektu, it has covered a proud road of training successors to the revolution who will stoutly carry forward the lineage of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@President Kim Il Sung with noble revolutionary comradeship and obligation had always remembered the revolutionary comrades who laid down their lives in the sacred war for the liberation of the country and directed deep attention to their children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@While guiding the construction of the school, he instructed officials that they should bring up at the school the helpless bereaved children of the revolutionaries who roamed about at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Under the wise guidance of the President Mangyongdae Revolutionary School was founded on October 12, Juche 36 (1947) as the successor to the Children's Corps School by inheriting the tradition of educating the bereaved children during the anti-Japanese revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Its institution marked the starting point of a new history of the Juche-based education of the bereaved children of the revolutionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@He gave on-the-spot guidance to the school on more than 110 occasions to indicate the road ahead of the school and directed a myriad of wealth of the country to the school for building it as a wonderful centre for the education of the bereaved children of the revolutionaries and looked after their living with the paternal care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Kim Jong Il has also paid deep attention to the work of the school. He visited the school on the New Year's Days of 1997 and 1998 to indicate the direction and way for improving the educational work and led it at every step so as to discharge its mission and duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Kim Jong Suk, anti-Japanese war hero, always found herself among the students of Mangyongdae Revolutionary School, upholding lofty intention of the President after the liberation of the country and took deep care of their study and life with parental warm affection and benevolence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Over the last six decades, Mangyongdae Revolutionary School has carried through the idea and policy of the Workers' Party of Korea on the education of the bereaved children of the revolutionaries and trained lots of hard cores of the revolution. Now its graduates are devoting themselves to the work for building a rich and strong country at different posts by inheriting the revolutionary spirit of their parents.

Military Attaches Corps Visits Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps here visited the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition on October 11 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round the immortal flowers Kimilsungia and Kimjongilia in full bloom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After seeing the flowers, Dau Xuan Long, military attache of the Vietnamese embassy here who is the doyen of the corps, wrote in the visitor's book that he believed the WPK holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem as its general secretary would always emerge victorious and the Korean people's desire for national reunification would surely be realized.

Struggle against Bourgeois Way of Life Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The bourgeois way of life is like dreadful ideological poison as it makes people degenerate and corrupt, says Rodong Sinmun Friday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The American way of life represents the corrupt bourgeois way of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the imperialist mode of existence based on all sorts of inhuman and miscellaneous ideas and modes including extreme individualism, the principle of existence governed by the jungle law, extreme misanthropy and national chauvinism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bourgeois way of life reduces people to human beings no better than animals who only seek their own interests and behave as they please and mental cripples who know nothing but money. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The virus of the above-said way of life lies in that it lures people into dissipation by stimulating their vulgar taste and sentiments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The virus of this way of life also lies in that it renders people deformed and benighted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The bourgeois way of life is of greater dangerous nature as it makes sensitive young people degenerate and corrupt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists and reactionaries consider the spread of the bourgeois way of life as a basic method of conducting operations for ideological and cultural poisoning. It has such awful virus as doing harm to the socialist way of life. This is because they eye aspects of everyday life of people which can easily be afflicted with the bourgeois way of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This way of life finds its way to aspects of everyday life of people bit by bit and develops with its roots taken, gnawing at the socialist life itself and making it corrupt and degenerate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historical experience goes to prove that grave consequences will be entailed by the failure to strictly guard against the infiltration of all unsound ways of life by the imperialists and wage a dynamic struggle against it.

Repeal of Unequal "Treaty" and U.S. Troop Pullout Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Members of civic and social organizations of south Korea including the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly held the 168th Friday meeting in front of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on Oct. 5 demanding the repeal of the south Korea-U.S. "mutual defence treaty" and withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution read out at the meeting said the "treaty" was unequal as it granted privileges and extraterritoriality to the U.S. forces occupying south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no ground for the "treaty" to exist any longer, the pact which imposes misfortunes and pain upon the people, while meeting the interests of the United States only, it said, adding: It is impossible to realize the desire of the Koreans for independence, peace and reunification as long as foreign forces are present in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "treaty" must be immediately scrapped and the U.S. forces be withdrawn from this land, it urged.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Mexico
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's famous work "On the Fundamentals of Revolutionary Party Building" was brought out in booklet by the Publishing House of the Workers' Party of Mexico on October 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Clearly expounded in the work, published on October 10, Juche 81(1992), are the historical lesson drawn from building a socialist ruling party, the fundamental principles of the building of Juche-type revolutionary party, and the matter of strengthening internationalist unity and solidarity of revolutionary parties.

WPK Founding Anniversary Observed in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Seminars were held in Pakistan, Bulgaria, France and Uzbekistan and Korean book and photo exhibitions and film shows took place in Laos, the Czech Republic, Uganda, Democratic Congo and Indonesia from Sept. 27 to Oct. 5 to mark the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venues of the functions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, books and photos showing their exploits in party building and Songun leadership and pictures introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Screened at the film shows were Korean films including "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Meets with Foreign Leaders and Famous Figures" and "Landscape of the Country Taking on More Beautiful Looks under the Leadership of the Great General".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the Pakistan Organization for Afro-Asian People's Solidarity told at the seminar that the WPK with Kim Jong Il as its general secretary would display its ever-victorious might in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-chairman of the National Internationalist Soldier Veterans Association of Uzbekistan said at the seminar that all the successes achieved in the DPRK were a brilliant fruition of Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The deputy secretary of the Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Youth Union noted he could deeply grasp through the film the sagacity of the leadership of Kim Jong Il and see the real appearance of Songun Korea that had changed under his care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The honorary chairman of the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association, the chairperson of the Ugandan National Women's Council and the president of the Working Citizens' Association of Democratic Congo highly praised the undying feats of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il in founding the WPK and developing it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, lectures explaining works of Kim Jong Il took place at Mongolian Chinggis Khan College and Literary College of Mongolia and a friendly meeting at the central palace of culture in Ulan Bator from Oct. 2 to 4 on the occasions of the 62nd anniversary of the WPK and the 81st anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the seminar in Pakistan and functions in Mongolia.

Group for Study of Songun Politics Formed in Germany
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of inaugurating the German group for the study of Songun politics took place on October 6 on the occasion of the 62nd anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venue of the ceremony were works of leader Kim Jong Il, photos showing his Songun leadership exploits and books and bulletins on the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Read out at the ceremony were congratulatory messages from groups for the study of Songun politics and organizations of friendship and solidarity with the Korean people in different countries, including the Switzerland-Korea Committee and the U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then, followed the speeches on the inauguration of the group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted there.

ATCC fustiga a los impedidores de avance de relaciones Corea-EE.UU.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de octubre (ATCC) -- En los ultimos dias, unos parlamentarios republicanos de Estados Unidos sometieron a la consideracion del congreso un proyecto de ley que objeta la eliminacion de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea en la lista de los "paises de apoyo al terrorismo".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La representante Ileana Ros-Lehtinen, quien tomo la iniciativa para formular el proyecto en cuestion, insistio en que la politica de EE.UU. con respecto a Corea no debe basarse en la esperanza de que esta sea fiel a su promesa sino en la accion real de ella y establecio en dicho proyecto los injustos condicionamientos tales como la "colaboracion en el dominio del desarrollo de los armamentos prohibidos" y la "cooperacion nuclear con Siria".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esto pone en peligro la perspectiva de las negociaciones en general contraviniendo a la tendencia de la epoca al alivio de tension en torno al problema nuclear de la Peninsula Coreana y frenando el avance de las conversaciones a 6 bandas y de las relaciones entre los dos paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Coincidiendo con la presentacion de este proyecto de ley por las fuerzas ultraconservadoras de EE.UU. Bush censuro sin ton ni son a la contraparte del dialogo en la escena internacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  No podemos pasar por alto las palabras descaradas del gobernante norteamericano.
�@En su discurso pronunciado el 25 de septiembre en la Asamblea General de la ONU, el gobernante norteamericano califico de "Poder barbaro" a ciertos paises incluyendo la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esto deviene un absurdo acto para denigrar la dignidad y la autoridad de la RPDC que se elevan de dia en dia en la escena internacional. Por lo tanto, el ejercito y el pueblo de Corea no lo perdonaran jamas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Si es asi el punto de vista del hombre en autoridad suprema de EE.UU. sobre la RPDC, ?como podemos evaluar la posicion de EE.UU. sobre Corea, que se cambia frecuentemente?, y ?como podemos hablar de la confianza reciproca que es el problema clave para el avance de las conversaciones a 6 partes y de las relaciones bilaterales?. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La solucion del problema nuclear mediante las negociaciones a 6 bandas es un problema politico muy agudo para la paz y la estabilidad de la Peninsula Coreana y la region de Asia-Pacifico. Por lo tanto, la confianza de los paises participantes resulta la vida para dar solucion al problema. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  No es casual que la sociedad internacional se preocupa de estos actos de las fuerzas ultraconservadoras norteamericanas que se toman precisamente cuando se logra un cierto avance de las conversaciones a 6 bandas y de las relaciones RPDC-EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tambien, en el pasado, cada vez que se lograba un avance del dialogo, las fuerzas ultraconservadoras norteamericanas salieron con diversos pretextos para poner obstaculos en la marcha de las conversaciones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Transcurrio mucho tiempo desde el inicio de las conversaciones a 6 bandas hasta la fecha sin cosechar resultado, lo cual se debe enteramente a la erronea posicion de EE.UU. con respecto a Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque ahora, EE.UU. debe reflexionar de los factores que ejercen influencias negativas sobre las conversaciones a 6 partes y el proceso de la solucion del problema nuclear y mantener la coherencia en su politica hacia Corea.

Kim Yong Il envia mensaje a su homologo jamaicano
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de octubre (ATCC) -- El premier del Consejo de Ministros de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Il, envio un mensaje de felicitacion a Bruce Golding por su nombramiento como primer ministro de Jamaica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El remitente expresa conviccion de que las relaciones de amistad entre los dos paises seguiran desarrollandose favorablemente y desea al destinatario exitos en su labor responsable para el desarrollo del pais y el bienestar del pueblo.
